vehicles.name: TGV PSE Bogie
vehicles.description: Bogie to put between every TGV PSE Car, except the power & end cars (which have their own bogies). Don't forget this or your train will look strange!

vehicles.name: TGV PSE Carmillon Cab (F) (P5)
vehicles.description:
Power car facing forwards, with the pantograph up to 5 blocks height.

France's original high-speed train, the TGV PSE, hit the rails in 1981. With its orange paint job and aerodynamic design, it changed rail travel by reaching speeds up to 300 km/h. Built specifically for the LGV Sud-Est route, the train features a streamlined nose, connected cars, and powerful electric motors that were quite revolutionary for their time.
